    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-01-08T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-01-08T15:00:00-05:00" n="858"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d858">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.6731/245a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kelley</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-01-08T15:00:00-05:00"
                            >January 8, 1938—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3. Please inform the Turkish Government that the formal notice of intention to
                    negotiate a trade agreement with Turkey referred to in the Department’s telegram
                    No. 109, December 23, 7 p.m.,<note n="2" xml:id="d858fn2">
                        <ref target="frus1937v02#pg_953">
                            <hi rend="italic">Ibid.</hi>, p. 953</ref>.</note> will be issued here
                    for publication in morning newspapers Wednesday, January 12.<note n="3"
                        xml:id="d858fn3">Department of State, <hi rend="italic">Press Releases</hi>,
                        January 15, 1938, p. 108.</note> Copies of announcement are being forwarded
                    to you by mail and are being given Turkish Embassy here.</p>
                <p>In accordance with our established procedure the formal notice states that the
                    final date for the receipt of briefs from interested persons with respect to
                    products to be considered is February 9, and oral hearings will open February
                    23. We would be able therefore to begin discussions with the Turkish delegation
                    here on or about March 1.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
